ics carry essential information that enables rich, re-            Pipe is the first open-source, re-runnable pipeline that produces\n                                        sponsive interaction, yet they are difficult to capture with           speaker-separated full-duplex dialogue speech at web scale,\n                                        conventional cascaded spoken dialogue systems [2], which               and the resulting DuplexChat (∼415k h) is the largest dialogue\n                                        serialize automatic speech recognition, text generation, and           resource to date (Table I). Our contributions are as follows:\n                                        speech synthesis [3]. Spoken Dialogue Language Models\n                                                                                                                 • We present an open-source pipeline named DuplexChat-\n                                        (SDLMs) such as dGSLM [4] and Moshi [5] address this\n                                                                                                                   Pipe which produces speaker-separated spoken dialogue\n                                        limitation by modeling the dialogue in an end-to-end manner,\n                                                                                                                   tracks for SDLM training.\n                                        making them a promising direction for more natural voice\n                                                                                                                 • We release DuplexChat, a spoken dialogue corpus com-\n                                        interaction.\n                                                                                                                   prising of 282,634 hours of English and 132,723 hours\n                                           As with text language models [6], SDLMs 