ext tokens while anchoring speech tokens with SFT, coupled with a rollout-reliability gating mechanism for stable updates.\n  3. Experiments across architectures and benchmarks show consistent gains in both semantic quality and acoustic expressiveness.\n\n=== 2604.15710 ===\n# VoxMind: An End-to-End Agentic Spoken Dialogue System\narXiv: 2604.15710\nAuthors: Tianle Liang, Yifu Chen, Shengpeng Ji, Yijun Chen, Zhiyang Jia, Jingyu Lu, Fan Zhuo, Xueyi Pu, Yangzhuo Li, Zhou Zhao\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_agent\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We formulate a formal definition for End-to-End Spoken Agents and propose VoxMind, a unified model that incorporates a \"Think-before-Speak\" paradigm to execute complex reasoning and tool-use tasks.\n  2. We construct AgentChat, a speech dataset annotated with reasoning trajectories, tool interactions, and complex planning paths to alleviate the scarcity of agentic supervision in spoken contexts.\n  3. We design a Multi-Agent Dynamic Tool Management architecture that employs an asynchronous parallel execution strategy to decouple inference latency from the size of the tool library.", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
